This is a list of all available assertions that come standard with cppunit.
Users can defin their own assertions to test special cases. refer to the
cppunit cookbook

To make use of these macros you need to include the following files
#include <cppunit/TestFixture.h>
#include <cppunit/extensions/HelperMacros.h>


Asserts that a specific exception was thrown.
CPPUNIT_TEST_EXCEPTION(function, exception)

Assertions that a condition is true.
CPPUNIT_ASSERT(condition)

Assertion with a user specified message.
CPPUNIT_ASSERT_MESSAGE(message, condition)

Fails with the specified message.
CPPUNIT_FAIL(message)
 
Asserts that two values are equals.
CPPUNIT_ASSERT_EQUAL(expected, actual)

Asserts that two values are equals, provides additional message on failure.
CPPUNIT_ASSERT_EQUAL_MESSAGE(message, expected, actual)

CPPUNIT_ASSERT_DOUBLES_EQUAL(expected, actual, delta)
Macro for primitive value comparisons.

